fields.Public Description:
Brantley is very calm most of the day and loves meeting new people. He is great with kids! We are simply looking for a home that will be able to love him well. He's a senior pup who is looking for his retirement home. He is neutered and up to date on his vaccinations. 

We adopted Brantley from a shelter. He was found on the streets and taken to the shelter with lacerations on his back they did not know what caused them but suspected it was an attack from another dog. While having Brantley in our family he has shown fear/hostility towards bigger dogs and is particularly scared of Huskies but has never attacked another dog/animal or person. 

Brantley also has the cocker spaniel cherry eye. When we rescued him, his veterinarian did not think he needed it removed, unless it was growing or bothering him. It has remained the same through the years. 

We will be moving into circumstances that force us to re-home Brantley and only hope his new family loves him at least as much as we do.


------------------------------------------------------

fields.Special Needs Info: Gracie is heartworm positive. She is currently on doxycycline and prednisone in preparation for heartworm treatment. I will pay for heartworm treatment.
fields.Public Description:
Gracie Update!! Gracie has been going to doggie daycare and the dog park several days per week, and is absolutely thriving in her socialization. She continues to have difficulty with our older terrier, Zeke, but she is able to successfully interact with dogs other than Zeke in other settings. She is best with dogs who are similarly high-energy. She is finished with heartworm treatment and her required rest period, has made a full recovery!! She is now ready to go to her forever home. 

Meet gorgeous, intelligent Gracie ll! She is a beautiful Belgian Malinois mix who is about a year old and about 32 pounds. She has the soulful brown eyes, the dark tip of her tail and ears, and the dark muzzle of a Belgian Malinois, but she is smaller than the typical Malinois, and her coat is so buttery-soft. She loves to be petted and to have her ears scratched. She is affectionate, playful, high-energy, extremely intelligent, and eager to please.

Gracie was a stray who was at Fort Worth Animal Control for two months before coming to stay with us. She loves her walks and although she doesn’t yet know how to heel, she is willing to walk at my (slow) pace and doesn’t pull at the leash. She also loves to play in the backyard, watching (and chasing) the squirrels and birds. She has not been destructive in either the yard or the house. She’ll play fetch with her toys, and she is learning to give up the toy so we can throw it!

According to animal control staff, Gracie was fine with other dogs. Unfortunately, I have an older terrier who has been the only dog for several years, and there’s been some friction between the two. Gracie would be best in a home without cats or small dogs. 

She’ll need walks and plenty of exercise, and she is so intelligent, so she’ll also need enrichment items. She loves puzzle toys and is really quick to solve them! She will likely need some obedience training for things like jumping up when she wants to play. Gracie is a little sensitive about being touched on her behind, but she has greatly improved since she’s been with us.

Gracie is spayed and fully housebroken, and she is current on her vaccinations. She is ready to find her forever home! Also, she has learned to coexist peacefully with our cat, but there is still friction between Gracie and our older terrier.

I fell in love with Gracie instantly, and I believe the right owner will too. She is an intelligent, affectionate companion who loves to exercise her body and her mind!

------------------------------------------------------

Name: willow
Breed: boston terrier staffie mix
Weight: 40 lbs
Bday approx.: sep. 12 2020
Age at intake: 1.5 years

Personality: willow is a lover of all people and is obsessed with being held. she is a snuggle bug, her favorite way to sleep is upside down under the blankets in bed with you! She loves to play with her people on her long leash in an open space.
She is dog selective so she makes pup friends who are submissive to her, and
around her size. she gets defensive if not. She has played with some kitties in the past. She is medium energy and loves to hide her favorite chew toys in silly places around the house (I found one in a fake plant lol). She loves kids and knows how to be gentle. Her favorite snack is turkey and her favorite toys are cat toys, she throws them in the air and catches them for hours. She does not have separation anxiety, but she will greet you at the door with love ready for belly rubs. She loves car rides and is very good at change. I moved twice with her and she was not anxious at all, as long as she has her people around she is never worried! She is very unique and will never fail to make you laugh.

Compatibility: willow has gotten along with pups her age and size in the past, but my mom’s dog tried to attack her and she has had social issues since then with dogs trying to set boundaries or indicting dominance. I would be wary introducing her to new pups and make sure to be in very open spaces with toys and treats! She does well on her own and a single-dog home with a family would be her ideal life. She has made kitty acquaintances before but has not had many interactions with them. She loves kids and adults, she gets along with all people.
